To study the influence of solvation—here by water—on the PBE0 results, we performed calculations using the Multipole Expansion (MPE) implicit solvation method as implemented in FHI-aims52 for the 31 k susbset. The MPE method facilitates an efficient treatment of the solvation effects on a solute, by using a continuum model of the solvent around it. In detail, the solute molecule is placed within a cavity with the dielectric permitivity of vacuum. The position of the cavity surface is determined by an iso-value \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
